definitions.definition: A large, naturally-occurring cavity formed underground or in the face of a cliff or a hillside.
examples: We found a cave on the mountainside where we could take shelter.

definitions.definition: A hole, depression, or gap in earth or rock, whether natural or man-made.
A storage cellar , especially for wine or cheese .
examples: This wine has been aged in our cave for thirty years.

definitions.definition: A place of retreat, such as a man cave .
examples: My room was a cozy cave where I could escape from my family.

definitions.definition: A naturally-occurring cavity in bedrock which is large enough to be entered by an adult.
examples: It was not strictly a cave , but a narrow fissure in the rock.

definitions.definition: A shielded area where nuclear experiments can be carried out.
Debris , particularly broken rock, which falls into a drill hole and interferes with drilling.
A group that breaks from a larger political party or faction on a particular issue.
Any hollow place, or part; a cavity.

main_definition: A large, naturally-occurring cavity formed underground or in the face of a cliff or a hillside.
